This paper deals with optimization of a generative model, specifically a discrete variational auto-encoder, using the Gumbel-Max reparameterization. This technique is commonly used in machine learning for continuous random variables, which suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with optimization of generative models, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of the Gumbel-Max reparameterization in this paper is also relevant to computer vision (cs.CV), as it is commonly used in image generation tasks. The paper also deals with learning latent representations, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with optimization of discrete variables, which is relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL), as discrete variables are commonly used in language modeling tasks.
